      "text": "Let the heav--ens re-joice; let earth-ly things be__ glad; for the Lord__ hath wrought might with His arm, He hath tram--pled up-on death by death. The first-born of the dead hath He be-come. From the bel-ly of Ha-des hath He de-liv-ered us, and hath grant--ed great mer-cy to the world. \n\nand hath grant-ed great mer-cy to the world.____"
